# WebhookRelay - Reliable Webhook Delivery System

## Project Context
Backend-only webhook delivery service:
- Producers POST events via API (API-key auth)
- Consumers register webhook URLs (JWT auth)
- Deliveries carry HMAC-SHA256 signed payloads
- Failures retry with exponential backoff (5 attempts)
- Exhausted deliveries become dead-letter, replayable manually
- Every attempt is logged
- 10 consecutive dead deliveries auto-disables an endpoint

## Tech Stack
Node.js + Express (ES modules), MongoDB + Mongoose, Redis + BullMQ,
JWT + bcryptjs + API keys, zod, express-rate-limit, swagger-ui-express,
Jest + Supertest + mongodb-memory-server, Docker.

## Architecture
Two processes, one codebase — src/server.js (Express API), src/worker.js (BullMQ delivery worker).

## Code Conventions (STRICT)
- ES modules, async/await only
- API responses: { success: boolean, data?: any, error?: string }
- Global error handler; controllers use next(err)
- Business logic in /services, queue setup in /queues, never in controllers
- AppError class (statusCode, message)
- kebab-case filenames
- All config via env through one config module
- Endpoint secrets returned ONCE at creation, never again, never logged
- Validate all input with zod middleware

## What NOT to Do
- Don't invent BullMQ APIs — say so if unsure
- No console.log (use logger)
- Comments explain WHY not WHAT

## Before Generating Code
1. Show a PLAN first.
2. Wait for approval.
3. Implement.
4. State assumptions.
